cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.SD, cs.CY, cs.CL

This paper analyzes content sharing between news sources, which involves natural language processing and information retrieval techniques (cs.IR). The study also involves network analysis and community detection (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper touches on topics related to social media and online communities (cs.SD), as well as ethics and policy implications of media polarization (cs.CY). Finally, the paper uses text classification and sentiment analysis to identify different narratives in news reporting (cs.CL).
